any tips on how to bring a baby up i'm a new mother and i need tips on how to bring a baby up thanks congrats have fun take a deep breath when you think you are about to burst take lots of photos they grow up sooooooo quick take advice from others think about it file it away in your head and use only what you think sounds okay ask for help when you need it it is not a sign of weekness or that you can't cope it shows that you love your child so much that you truly want the best for it a mothers instinct is usually always right go with it if it is the middle of the night you have had about seconds sleep in the last days and you don't feel like you have any mothering instincts it is only because you are tired not because you are a bad mother each night as you put your child down recall your day tell your child all about their day and why you enjoyed spending it with them even on days you think were bad in hindsight you can recall the cuddles smiles early recognition of who you are etc don't stress yourself with housework if you are tired and your baby is asleep go and have a sleep don't be afraid of offending people by putting a no visitors please sign on your door or taking the phone off the hook take every opportunity to bond with your child cuddles and kisses are the days memories that you fall asleep thinking about oh and invest in a baby monitor Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Shaggy dog story Sleep The Beach Boys Jon Secada Kurt Cobain Tupac Shakur About a Boy Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Elephant The Shining (film) Kodocha The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind One Tree Hill (TV series) Characters in the Smurfs Friends Knots Landing EastEnders Childbirth The Amber Spyglass History of As the World Turns (2000-present) The Fairly OddParents Journey (band) 2005 trial of Michael Jackson Lauren Bacall The Ashlee Simpson Show Kimi Finster Frankie Laine Happy Tree Friends Doug Cat Urinary incontinence The Catcher in the Rye P